data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value: Bill Bourbon's business partner and close freind. Crawdad claims Bourbon used many of his connections to start his business, but never gave Crawdad enough credit for it financially. Business matters asside, Crawdad reports that Bill was a good freind, and a good man. He mourns over the loss of his freind, and hopes they catch the murderer. Crawdad also reports that in the months leading up to the murder, Bill would show up to work under the influence, always saying he had "stopped by Nathaniel's bar."
